<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1058,746,827]" pageId="16" pageNumber="975">
D i a g n o s i s: These specimens have a yellow cranium and the pronotum is widely yellow at the sides. These characteristics will distinguish the members of this species from congeners. The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Opitz" authorityYear="2006" box="[433,533,805,826]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Amboakis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="977" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[433,533,805,826]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="975">Amboakis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
OPITZ was established in 2006 (OPITZ 2006).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1059,842,1128]" pageId="16" pageNumber="975">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Size: Length 4.0 mm; width 
<quantity box="[673,753,842,864]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="16" pageNumber="975" unit="mm" value="1.1">1.1 mm</quantity>
. Form: As in 
<figureCitation box="[895,980,842,864]" captionStart="Figs 282-285" captionStartId="98.[151,191,1506,1528]" captionTargetBox="[153,1059,199,1489]" captionTargetId="figure@98.[153,1059,199,1491]" captionTargetPageId="98" captionText="Figs 282-285: Habitus; (282) Parapelonides naranjo; (283) Pyticara frontegalba; (284) Amboakis bermejo; (285) A. collucoatis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746802/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="975">Fig. 284</figureCitation>
. Color: Cranium testaceous; antenna black; prothorax bicolorous, venter and pronotal sides yellow, pronotal disc with brown streak; pterothorax and elytra brown, except elytron with a faint paler region behind middle; legs mostly testaceous, tibiae infuscated. Head: Cranium finely punctate; antenna (
<figureCitation box="[528,607,959,981]" captionStart="Figs 61-91" captionStartId="73.[151,191,1343,1365]" captionTargetBox="[151,1033,198,1310]" captionTargetId="figure@73.[151,1059,198,1328]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="Figs 61-91: Antennae; (61) Madoniella muralla; (62) M. nota; (63) M. acicula; (64) M. aspera; (65) M. baja; (66) M. delta; (67) Amboakis bermejo; (68) Pujoliclerus variolus; (69) Megatrachys irrasis; (70) Cregya arima; (71) Nelsopelonium aspikelum; (72) Cregya vicosa; (73) Pujoliclerus abditus; (74) P. dexus; (75) Cregya triguttula; (76) Pyticeroides brevitubulus; (77) Pujoliclerus lasiosus; (78) Cregya biguttula; (79) Sirpa acara; (80) Parapelonides naranjo; (81) Cregya livida; (82) Amboakis collucoatis; (83) Ampleris jatai; (84) Megaphloeus yasuni; (85) Pelonium implacide, male; (86) Epiphloeus prolixicornus; (87) Pelonium implacide, female; (88) Epiphloeus mantillerii; (89) Amboakis mitaraka; (90) Ellipotoma makrosa; (91) Cregya maura." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746752" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746752/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="975">Fig. 67</figureCitation>
) capitate, funicular antennomeres slightly triangular, capitular antennomeres 8 and 9 triangular, antennomere 10 ovoid; eyes large, coarsely facetted, eye wider than frons (EW/FW 22/15). Thorax: Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[961,1051,1018,1040]" captionStart="Figs 179-193" captionStartId="81.[151,191,1359,1381]" captionTargetBox="[167,1032,201,1342]" captionTargetId="figure@81.[152,1058,201,1346]" captionTargetPageId="81" captionText="Figs 179-193: Pronota; 179) Phonius versus; (180) Perilypus arsus; (181) A. nodus; (182) Pyticara frontegalba; (183) Pelonium implacide; (184) Neorthoplera quintana; (185) Perilypus virgulatus; (186) P. alpinus; (187) Amboakis expandosa; (188) Ampleris jatai; (189) Megaphloeus jasuni; (190) Amboakis bermejo (191) Madoniella delta; (192) Megaphloeus imparilus; (193) Pyticeroides brevitubulus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746768" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746768/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="975">Fig. 190</figureCitation>
) transverse (PW/PL 50/40), disc finely punctate; pronotal tubercle well developed; elytral asetiferous punctures organized into 10 striae (EL/EW 180/45). Abdomen: Pygidium transverse 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[254,261,1106,1128]" pageId="16" pageNumber="975">/</emphasis>
scutiform; aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation box="[524,615,1106,1128]" captionStart="Figs 213-218" captionStartId="85.[151,191,1262,1284]" captionTargetBox="[153,1061,202,1251]" captionTargetId="figure@85.[153,1061,202,1251]" captionTargetPageId="85" captionText="Figs 213-218: Aedeagi; (213) Perilypus virgulatus; (214) Agnatis curvabilis; (215) A. vaurieae; (216) Parapelonides naranjo; (217) Pyticara frontegalba; (218) Amboakis bermejo." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746776" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746776/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="975">Fig. 218.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
